headlines.description: — Myles Turner scored 27 points, Tyrese Haliburton had 18 points and 13 assists and the Indiana Pacers held off the Cleveland Cavaliers 121-116 on Friday night to open the NBA’s inaugural In-Season Tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Turner, Haliburton help Pacers beat Cavaliers 121-116 in In-Season Tournament opener

events.name: New York Knicks at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard made big shots down the stretch and Brook Lopez blocked shots on the other end of the floor all night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard delivers down the stretch to help the Bucks outlast the Knicks 110-105

headlines.description: — New court, new uniforms and, the Miami Heat hope, a new start.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyler Herro scores 24 points, Heat top Wizards 121-114 in tournament opener

headlines.description: — Whether the new In-Season Tournament gives early regular-season games like this a little extra meaning, Brooklyn's Dorian Finney-Smith was sure of a few things.
headlines.shortLinkText: Finney-Smith scores 21 points, Mikal Bridges adds 20 in Nets' 109-107 victory over Bulls

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — The Golden State Warriors and the Oklahoma City Thunder gave the NBA exactly what it wanted out of the inaugural In-Season Tournament — playoff-caliber intensity early in the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry makes last-second layup to give Warriors 141-139 win over Thunder in tourney opener

headlines.description: — The only thing brighter than Denver's new vibrant blue-and-yellow floor was the shooting performance of Nikola Jokic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic scores 33 points, leads Nuggets to 125-114 win over Mavericks in NBA tournament opener

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Shaedon Sharpe's cold made his voice a bit raspy, but it didn't impact his sense of humor.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trail Blazers open the new In-Season Tournament with a 115-113 win over the Grizzlies in overtime
